|GOC 2nd New Zealand Division]]|years=1939\u20131945}}\n{{s-aft|after=Post disbanded}}\n|-\n{{s-bef|before=[[Brian Horrocks]]}}\n{{s-ttl|title=[[X Corps (United Kingdom)|GOC X Corps]]|years=April \u2013 May 1943}}\n{{s-aft|after=[[Richard McCreery]]}}\n|-\n{{S-gov}}\n{{Succession box | before=[[Cyril Newall, 1st Baron Newall|Sir Cyril Newall]]| title=[[Governor-General of New Zealand]] | years=1946\u20131952 | after=[[Charles Norrie, 1st Baron Norrie]]}}\n{{S-reg|uk}}\n{{Succession box | title=[[Baron Freyberg]] | before=New creation | after=[[Paul Freyberg, 2nd Baron Freyberg|Paul Freyberg]] | years=1951\u20131963}}\n{{S-end}}\n{{Governors-General of New Zealand}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Freyberg, Bernard}}\n[[Category:1889 births]]\n[[Category:1963 deaths]]\n[[Category:Barons in the Peerage of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Battle of the Somme recipients of the Victoria Cross]]\n[[Category:British Army personnel of World War I]]\n[[Category:British Army generals of World War II]]\n[[Category:Queen's Royal Regiment officers]]\n[[Category:Grenadier Guards officers]]\n[[Category:Manchester Regiment officers]]\n[[Category:Crete in World War II]]\n[[Category:People educated at Wellington College (New Zealand)]]\n[[Category:Governors-General of New Zealand]]\n[[Category:International Olympic Committee members]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Croix de Guerre 1914\u20131918 (France)]]\n[[Category:Commanders of the Legion of Merit]]\n[[Category:Grand Commanders of the Order of George I with Swords]]\n[[Category:Knights Commander of the Order of the British Empire]]\n[[Category:Knights Commander of the Order of the Bath]]\n[[Category:Knights Grand Cross of the Order of St Michael and St George]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the War Cross (Greece)]]\n[[Category:Recipients of the Cross of Valour (Greece)]]\n[[Category:New Zealand generals]]\n[[Category:New Zealand military personnel of World War II]]\n[[Category:New Zealand sports executives and administrators